'''约瑟夫·阿萊斯·克里普斯'''（{{lang-de|Josef Alois Krips}}，{{bd|1902年|4月8日|1974年|5月16日|catIdx=Krips, Josef}}），[[奧地利|奧地利]]指揮家，小提琴家。

== 生平 ==
1902年，约瑟夫·阿萊斯·克里普斯出生於[[維也納|維也納]]，繼而成為{{link-en|優西比烏·曼第澤夫斯基|Eusebius Mandyczewski|曼第澤夫斯基}}和[[费利克斯·魏因加特纳|魏因加特纳]]的徒弟<ref name=WienerPhil>{{cite web |author=Vienna Philharmonic |title=100th birthday of Josef Krips |url=https://www.wienerphilharmoniker.at/orchestra/philharmonic-journal/year/2002/month/4/blogitemid/348 |access-date=2017-08-02 |work=Vienna Philharmonic |archive-date=2020-10-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201003080119/https://www.wienerphilharmoniker.at/orchestra/philharmonic-journal/year/2002/month/4/blogitemid/348 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Berkshire>{{cite web |title=1969 Berkshire Festival |publisher=Boston Symphony Orchestra |year=1969 |page=34 |url=http://worldcat.org/digitalarchive/content/server15982.contentdm.oclc.org/BSYMO/PROG/TRUSVolume14/Pub412_1969_TWD_Wk06_Sat.pdf |access-date=2017-08-21 |archive-date=2017-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170822052301/http://worldcat.org/digitalarchive/content/server15982.contentdm.oclc.org/BSYMO/PROG/TRUSVolume14/Pub412_1969_TWD_Wk06_Sat.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Brooklyn>{{cite web |title=The Conductor |publisher=Brooklyn Academy of Music |date=February 1972 |url=http://levyarchive.bam.org/Detail/DownloadRepresentation/context/objects/representation_id/65080/id/62156/download/1/version/original |access-date=2017-08-21 |archive-date=2017-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170822052348/http://levyarchive.bam.org/Detail/DownloadRepresentation/context/objects/representation_id/65080/id/62156/download/1/version/original |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Terkel>{{cite book |last=Terkel |first=Studs |title=And They All Sang: Adventurs of an Eclectic Disk Jockey |publisher=The New Press |location=New York |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hsaIG4lSOyYC&q=%22i+was+a+pupil+of+felix+weingartner%22&pg=PA39 |page=39 |access-date=2017-08-15 |year=2005 |isbn=9781595586551 |archive-date=2021-08-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210812191653/https://books.google.com/books?id=hsaIG4lSOyYC&q=%22i+was+a+pupil+of+felix+weingartner%22&pg=PA39 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Hutchinson>{{cite web |work=Hutchinson's Biography Database |publisher=Helicon Publishing |title=Josef Krips |year=2011 |url=http://web.a.ebscohost.com/ehost/detail/detail?vid=0&sid=d6be04ad-e77c-4f23-b188-d49bdee59b69%40sessionmgr4008&bdata=JnNpdGU9ZWhvc3QtbGl2ZQ%3d%3d#AN=59154311&db=khh |access-date=2017-08-18}}</ref>。1921至1924年間，在[[维也纳人民歌剧院|維也納民俗歌劇院]]擔當魏因加特纳的助理和合唱隊的總監。其後克里普斯成為了不同樂隊的指揮，如在1926至1933年間，成為[[卡尔斯鲁厄|卡尔斯鲁厄]]當地樂團的音樂總監。1933年回歸維也納，擔任民俗歌劇院的常駐指揮，也經常在[[维也纳国立歌剧院|國立歌劇院]]指揮<ref name=Berkshire/><ref name=Brooklyn/>。1935年成為[[维也纳美术学院|維也納藝術學院]]教授，並開始每年在[[萨尔茨堡音乐节|萨尔茨堡音乐节]]上指揮音樂會，直至1938年<ref name=WienerPhil/>。

雖然自幼是[[天主教|天主教]]徒，但由於父親是猶太人，因此克里普斯在[[德奧合併|德奧合併]]後，離開了[[維也納|維也納]]，移居[[貝爾格萊德|貝爾格萊德]]，以免無法繼續指揮生涯<ref name=Ewen>{{cite book |last=Ewen |first=David |title=Musicians Since 1900 |publisher=Wilson |page=426 |year=1978 |isbn=9780824205652 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VV0YAAAAIAAJ&q=%22My+mother+was+Catholic,+so+were+her+parents%22 |access-date=2017-08-15 |archive-date=2021-08-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210811082606/https://books.google.com/books?id=VV0YAAAAIAAJ&q=%22My+mother+was+Catholic,+so+were+her+parents%22 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=McFadden>{{cite web |title=Josef Krips, the Conductor, Dies of Cancer in Geneva |author=McFadden, Robert D. |work=New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1974/10/14/archives/josef-krips-the-conductor-dies-of-cancer-in-geneva-make-musicians.html |date=1974-10-14 |access-date=2017-08-18 |archive-date=2021-07-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210712120955/https://www.nytimes.com/1974/10/14/archives/josef-krips-the-conductor-dies-of-cancer-in-geneva-make-musicians.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Œsterreichisches>{{cite web |title=Krips, Brüder |publisher=Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften |work=Oesterreichisches Musiklexikon online |url=http://www.musiklexikon.ac.at/ml/musik_K/Krips_Brueder.xml |date=n.d. |access-date=2017-08-23 |archive-date=2021-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221224943/https://www.musiklexikon.ac.at/ml/musik_K/Krips_Brueder.xml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但克里普斯也只能在貝爾格萊德的歌劇院和愛樂管弦樂團工作一年多，南斯拉夫便淪為德軍佔領，餘下的戰爭歲月，克里普斯便在食品工廠擔當工人渡過<ref name=Ewen/><ref name=Berkshire/><ref name=WienerPhil/><ref name=Prodhan>{{cite web |last=Prodhan |first=Georgina |title=Vienna Philharmonic acknowledges honoring Nazi war criminal |publisher=Reuters |work=Reuters.com |date=2013-03-10 |access-date=2017-08-15 |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/entertainment-us-austria-orchestra-nazis-idUSBRE9280I820130311 |archive-date=2021-07-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210711220458/https://www.reuters.com/article/entertainment-us-austria-orchestra-nazis-idUSBRE9280I820130311 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Vigeland>{{cite web |last=Vigeland |first=Carl |date=1995-08-16 |title=The Human Side of Conductor Josef Krips |work=The Buffalo News |access-date=2017-08-02 |url=http://buffalonews.com/1995/08/27/the-human-side-of-conductor-josef-krips/ |archive-date=2018-05-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180531191822/http://buffalonews.com/1995/08/27/the-human-side-of-conductor-josef-krips/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Brown>{{cite book |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |location=Lanham, MD |author=Brown, Emily Freeman |title=A Dictionary for the Modern Conductor |year=2015 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=k9SOCgAAQBAJ&q=%22josef+krips%22++%22san+francisco%22+%22buffalo%22&pg=PA186 |page=186 |isbn=9780810884014 |access-date=2017-08-02 |archive-date=2021-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210710114052/https://books.google.com/books?id=k9SOCgAAQBAJ&q=%22josef+krips%22++%22san+francisco%22+%22buffalo%22&pg=PA186 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Peress">{{cite book |last=Peress |first=Maurice |title=Maverick Maestro |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KrIYDQAAQBAJ&q=krips+%22food+factory%22+%22maverick+maestro%22&pg=PT187 |publisher=Routledge |year=2016 |location=Milton Park |isbn=9781315478951 |access-date=2017-08-02 |archive-date=2021-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210815005055/https://books.google.com/books?id=KrIYDQAAQBAJ&q=krips+%22food+factory%22+%22maverick+maestro%22&pg=PT187 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。

戰爭結束後，克里普斯1945年回到奧地利。由於未曾為納粹政權服務，成為第一批獲盟軍批准工作的指揮家之一，更成為戰後，首位指揮[[维也纳爱乐乐团|维也纳爱乐乐团]]和在薩爾茨堡音樂節指揮的指揮家<ref name=WienerPhil/><ref name=Buffalo>{{cite web |title=Josef Krips BPO Music Director: 1954-1963 |work=Buffalo Philharmonic Orchestra |url=http://archives.bpo.org/krips.htm |access-date=2017-08-02 |author=Buffalo Philharmonic Orchestra |archive-date=2021-07-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210712013836/https://archives.bpo.org/krips.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。更因[[克萊門斯·克勞斯|克萊門斯·克勞斯]]被盟軍禁演，克利普斯得以指揮了1946和1947年兩屆[[維也納新年音樂會|維也納新年音樂會]]。之後，他和克勞斯與[[卡爾·貝姆|貝姆]]致力於將維也納國立歌劇院的演出回復至戰前水平。

1950至1954年間，克里普斯成為[[伦敦交响乐团|伦敦交响乐团]]的首席指揮，其後成為{{link-en|水牛城愛樂樂團|Buffalo Philharmonic Orchestra}}的首席指揮和[[舊金山交響樂團|舊金山交響樂團]]的音樂總監（1963年–1970年）<ref name=Buffalo/><ref>{{cite web |last=Stewart |first=Andrew |url=https://lso.co.uk/orchestra/history/recordings.html |title=London Symphony Orchestra -- Recordings |publisher=London Symphony Orchestra |year=2004 |access-date=2017-08-21 |archive-date=2022-03-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324212055/https://lso.co.uk/orchestra/history/recordings.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Trotter>{{cite journal |last=Trotter |first=Herman |title=The Buffalo Philharmonic |journal=American Record Guide |volume=56 |issue=3 |date=May–June 1993 |page=14+ |url=http://go.galegroup.com/ps/retrieve.do?tabID=T003&resultListType=RESULT_LIST&searchResultsType=SingleTab&searchType=BasicSearchForm&currentPosition=3&docId=GALE%7CA13850497&docType=Article&sort=DA-ASC-SORT&contentSegment=&prodId=GPS&contentSet=GALE%7CA13850497&searchId=R1&userGroupName=lln_ptamm&inPS=true |access-date=2017-08-18}}</ref><ref name=Trotter2>{{cite journal |journal=American Record Guide |last=Trotter |first=Herman |title=Buffalo's new conductor |volume=62 |issue=1 |date=January–February 1999 |page=16+ |url=http://go.galegroup.com/ps/retrieve.do?tabID=T003&resultListType=RESULT_LIST&searchResultsType=SingleTab&searchType=BasicSearchForm&currentPosition=15&docId=GALE%7CA53709878&docType=Article&sort=DA-ASC-SORT&contentSegment=&prodId=GPS&contentSet=GALE%7CA53709878&searchId=R1&userGroupName=lln_ptamm&inPS=true |access-date=2017-08-18}}</ref><ref name=Goldman>{{cite web |author=Goldman, Mary Kunz |title=Encore for Josef Krips; He was the BPO's longest-running music director next to JoAnn Falletta -- and the world is rediscovering his unique gifts. |work=The Buffalo News |date=2012-03-17 |url=http://buffalonews.com/2012/03/18/encore-for-josef-krips-he-was-the-bpos-longest-running-music-director-next-to-joann-falletta-and-the-world-is-rediscovering-his-unique-gifts/ |access-date=2017-08-02 |archive-date=2017-08-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802204952/http://buffalonews.com/2012/03/18/encore-for-josef-krips-he-was-the-bpos-longest-running-music-director-next-to-joann-falletta-and-the-world-is-rediscovering-his-unique-gifts/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Hennion>{{cite web |title=San Francisco's Orchestra Seeking 1.2 Million Raise |work=Chicago Tribune |author=Hennion, Reeve |url=http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1965/01/16/page/11/article/san-franciscos-orchestra-seeking-1-2-million-raise |date=1965-01-16 |access-date=2017-08-02 |archive-date=2017-08-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803012742/http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1965/01/16/page/11/article/san-franciscos-orchestra-seeking-1-2-million-raise/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=SF>{{cite web |title=From the Archives: Podcasts |work=San Francisco Symphony |author=San Francisco Symphony |url=https://www.sfsymphony.org/Watch-Listen-Learn/Podcasts-and-Music/Archives-Podcast |access-date=2017-08-02 |archive-date=2019-12-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218060536/https://www.sfsymphony.org/Watch-Listen-Learn/Podcasts-and-Music/Archives-Podcast |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Life>{{cite web |title=Life Guide |work=Life |date=1963-11-01 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VlIEAAAAMBAJ&q=%22josef+krips%22++%22san+francisco%22+%22buffalo%22&pg=PA17 |access-date=2017-08-02 |archive-date=2021-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210815005057/https://books.google.com/books?id=VlIEAAAAMBAJ&q=%22josef+krips%22++%22san+francisco%22+%22buffalo%22&pg=PA17 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=IndRec>{{cite web |title=Ramsey Lewis Set For Appearance With Toronto Symphony Orchestra |date=1968-06-23 |access-date=2017-08-04 |url=https://newspapers.library.in.gov/cgi-bin/imageserver.pl?oid=INR19680323-01&getpdf=true |work=Indianapolis Recorder |archive-date=2021-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210710115018/https://newspapers.library.in.gov/cgi-bin/imageserver.pl?oid=INR19680323-01&getpdf=true |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而他自1963年[[倫敦皇家歌劇院|倫敦皇家歌劇院]]和1966年[[紐約|紐約]][[大都會歌劇院|大都會歌劇院]]的首次登台後，便是這兩大歌劇院的常客。1968年初次指揮[[波士顿交响乐团|波士顿交响乐团]]<ref name=Berkshire/>。1970年克里普斯成為[[柏林德意志歌劇院|柏林德意志歌劇院]]的藝術總監。而在1970至1973年間，他成為了[[维也纳交响乐团|维也纳交响乐团]]的藝術顧問。

克里普斯1974年因肺癌逝世於[[瑞士|瑞士]][[日內瓦|日內瓦]]，享年72歲<ref name=McFadden/><ref>{{cite journal |year=1974 |title=Josef Krips: Obituary |journal=The Musical Times |volume=vol. 115 |issue=no. 1582 |pages=pp. 1071 |accessdate=}}</ref><ref name=Reuters>{{cite web |agency=Reuters |title=Famed Conductor Josef Krips Dies |work=Chicago Tribune |url=http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1974/10/14/page/86/article/famed-conductor-josef-krips-dies |date=1974-10-14 |access-date=2017-08-02 |archive-date=2017-08-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803014359/http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1974/10/14/page/86/article/famed-conductor-josef-krips-dies/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Gestorben Josef Krips |url=http://www.spiegel.de/spiegel/print/d-41599129.html |work=Der Spiegel |date=1974-10-21|access-date=2017-08-02}}</ref>。

